<bdy>

A <b>goutte</b> is a droplet-shaped <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../126/921126.xml">
charge</link> used in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../610/13610.xml">
heraldry</link>.  Its name derives from the <language wordnetid="106282651" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../082/320082.xml">
Old French</link></language>
 for "droplet".<p>

A goutte may be <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../365/7954365.xml">
blazon</link>ed by its <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../995/368995.xml">
tincture</link>, as in a <it>goutte argent</it> (literally "a silver droplet").  Alternatively, there are special names given to gouttes of various tinctures, as in a <it>goutte d'eau</it> (literally "a droplet of water").</p>
